data.name: labelScreenshotsFolderHelp.Text
data.value: This folder path will be used for the location of where screenshots will be saved. It will have initially been defined by the configuration file but you can change it here for your own purposes. A new Screen or Region that you add will use this folder path by default.

data.name: labelFilenamePatternHelp.Text
data.value: This filename pattern will be used when screenshots are saved. It will have initially been defined by the configuration file but you can change it here for your own purposes. You can use macro tags but some macro tags may not parse correctly in the preview shown here.

data.name: labelImageFormatHelp.Text
data.value: Choose an image format which will be used during a screen capture session. The default image format will have been defined by the configuration file but you can change it here so that each new Screen and Region added will use the selected image format.

data.name: labelLimitHelp.Text
data.value: Sets a limit on the number of screen capture cycles. For example, with this option enabled and the numeric value set to 5, it will be five screen capture cycles until the limit is reached. This option is commonly used with the Limit Reached condition of a Trigger.

data.name: labelInitialCaptureHelp.Text
data.value: When this option is enabled an initial set of screenshots will be taken before the first cycle of screenshots so that screenshots are taken immediately when a screen capture session starts. Disabling this option will wait for the first cycle of screenshots at the set interval.

data.name: labelIntervalHelp.Text
data.value: Define the interval at which screenshots should be taken. The cycles can be as fast or as slow as you want. The timer starts when the Start Screen Capture button is clicked, the Start Screen Capture menu option is selected, or a scheduled start time is encountered.

data.name: labelOptimizeScreenCaptureHelp.Text
data.value: Determine if the screen capture session should be optimized. If it is optimized then the new image captured is compared with any previous image (or the last image) captured and, if the image is exactly the same, then the screenshot will not be saved.

data.name: labelScreenshotLabelHelp.Text
data.value: You can apply a label to each screenshot taken so that you can filter by that label when reviewing screenshots. Type your label in the text field "Screenshot Label", click the "Add To List" button, and ensure the "Apply this label to each screenshot" option is enabled.

data.name: textBoxRegularExpressionHelp.Text
data.value:
Regular Expression Help
[abc] A single character of a, b, or c [^abc] A character except a, b, or c [a-z] A character in the range a-z [a-zA-Z] A character in the range a-z or A-Z a|b Match either a or b a? Zero or one instance of a a* Zero or more instances of a a+ One or more instances of a a{3} Exactly 3 of a a{3,6} Between 3 and 6 of a ^ Start of text $ End of text
Examples ^.{3}$ will match any 3 characters ^(A|a)pple$ will match "Apple" or "apple" ^colou?r$ matches "color" or "colour" ^\(\d{3}\)-\d{3}-\d{4}$ is a phone number in Canada using the format (xxx)-xxx-xxxx ^[\w.\-]{1,25}@(yahoo|hotmail|gmail)\.com$ will match any email address using Yahoo, Hotmail, or Gmail

data.name: labelActiveWindowTitleHelp.Text
data.value: Compare the provided text with the active window title. You can choose to either have the text match against the active window title or not match with the active window title. There are case sensitive match and case insensitive match options. Using a "Case Sensitive Match" will consider lowercase and uppercase characters in the exact order. Using a "Case Insensitive Match" considers characters in the exact order but not necessarily using the exact case. A "Regular Expression Match" uses a regex pattern for the comparison instead of text.

data.name: labelApplicationFocusHelp.Text
data.value: When enabled, you can have an application's process be focused on during the time a screenshot is taken. Select a process from the list then adjust the delay before and after the focus is set (in milliseconds). Use the "Test" button to test the application focus functionality. Use the "Refresh" button to refresh the list with the currently running processes.

data.name: labelSecurityHelp.Text
data.value: This passphrase will be required for Show Interface, Stop Screen Capture, and Exit Application. The system tray icon menus will also be limited. Enter a passphrase and click Set Passphrase. Click on Clear Passphrase to not use a passphrase and remove all restrictions.
